    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <div id="faq" class="py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="lg:text-center mb-16">
                <h2 class="text-base text-blue-600 font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase">FAQ</h2>
                <p class="mt-2 text-3xl leading-8 font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">
                    Frequently Asked Questions
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-6">
                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-left focus:outline-none">
                        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Is my salary data secure?</span>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-blue-500 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 hidden">
                        <p class="text-gray-600">
                            Absolutely. Meeting Meter uses bank-level encryption for all salary data. We never store raw salary information—only calculated hourly rates. You maintain full control over who can view and edit salary data within your organization.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-left focus:outline-none">
                        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">How does the salary calculation work?</span>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-blue-500 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 hidden">
                        <p class="text-gray-600">
                            We calculate hourly rates by dividing annual salaries by 2,080 working hours (52 weeks × 40 hours). For contractors or part-time employees, you can input custom hourly rates. The meeting cost is then calculated by multiplying each attendee's hourly rate by the meeting duration.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-left focus:outline-none">
                        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">What if I don't know exact salaries?</span>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-blue-500 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 hidden">
                        <p class="text-gray-600">
                            No problem! You can use industry-standard salary benchmarks by role and location. Many teams find these estimates valuable even without exact numbers. As you gather more precise data, you can update individual salaries.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-left focus:outline-none">
                        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Does this work with Outlook or other calendars?</span>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-blue-500 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 hidden">
                        <p class="text-gray-600">
                            Currently, Meeting Meter only supports Google Calendar. We're actively working on Outlook integration, which will launch in Q4 2023. Join our mailing list to be notified when it's available.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
                    <button class="w-full flex justify-between items-center p-6 text-left focus:outline-none">
                        <span class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Can I try before I buy?</span>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-blue-500 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="px-6 pb-6 hidden">
                        <p class="text-gray-600">
                            Yes! Our free plan supports teams up to 5 people with full functionality. For larger teams, we offer a 14-day free trial of our Growth plan with no credit card required.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
